deck: A tattoo artist who befriended Howard the Duck. Tara has shapeshifting powers.
description:
Origin

Tara Tam was a regular girl whom did not get along with her parents very much. Everything changed however when Tara gained the powers of a shapeshifter by eating meat that was made out of Skrulls whom had changed themselves into cows.

Creation

Tara Tam was created by Chip Zdarsky and Joe Quinones and first appeared in Howard the Duck Volume 3 issue 1 (2015).

Major Story Arcs

Meeting Howard

Tara Tam had moved out of her parents' house and started a tatoo shop. She first met Howard the Duck when they where both in prison due to minor offences. When they both left jail, the two started an unlikely friendship.

deck: The son of Darren Cross, the former CEO of Cross Technological Enterprises.
description:
Origin

Augustine is the son of the late Darren Cross, and inherited Cross Technological Enterprises upon his father's death.

Creation

Augustine Cross was created by David Michelinie and John Romita Jr. and first appeared in Iron Man Vol.1 issue 145 (1981).

Major Story Arcs

Meeting Iron Man

At one point he was thought to be a suspect in an incident where the Raiders were hired to attack Iron Man, but turned out to be innocent.

In Miami versus Ant-Man

Years later, he resurfaces in Miami, where he arranges the kidnappings of Erica Sondheim and Cassie Lang in order to resurrect his father.
name: Augustine Cross
